      "content": "It makes complete sense that seeking help feels like a performance when your internal reality is so fractured and hopeless. The fear that you might be permanently broken and that recovery is just a lie people tell to make themselves feel better is a very real and painful burden to carry. You are not a lost cause, even if it feels that way right now, because the desire to believe otherwise suggests a part of you is still reaching out for anything that might fix this.",
